TY  - JOUR
AU  - Lagos, Ricardo
T1  - A Model of TFP
PY  - 2006
Y1  - 2006/10/01
DO  - 10.1111/j.1467-937X.2006.00405.x
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 73
IS  - 4
SP  - 983
EP  - 1007
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper proposes an aggregative model of total factor productivity (TFP) in the spirit of Houthakker (1955–1956). It considers a frictional labour market where production units are subject to idiosyncratic shocks and jobs are created and destroyed as in Mortensen and Pissarides (1994). An aggregate production function is derived by aggregating across micro-production units in equilibrium. The level of TFP is explicitly shown to depend on the underlying distribution of shocks as well as on all the characteristics of the labour market as summarized by the job-destruction decision. The model is also used to study the effects of labour-market policies on the level of measured TFP.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1467-937X.2006.00405.x
ER  - 



