T1  - Monotone Equilibrium in Multi-Unit Auctions
PY  - 2006
Y1  - 2006/10/01
DO  - 10.1111/j.1467-937X.2006.00407.x
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 73
IS  - 4
SP  - 1039
EP  - 1056
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - In two-sided multi-unit auctions having a variety of payment rules, including uniform-price and discriminatory auctions, a monotone pure-strategy equilibrium (MPSE) exists when bidders are risk neutral with independent multi-dimensional types and interdependent values. In fact, all mixed-strategy equilibria are ex post allocation and interim expected payment equivalent to MPSE. Thus, for standard expected surplus/revenue analysis, there is no loss restricting attention to monotone strategies.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1467-937X.2006.00407.x
ER  - 



